**The week's dominant stories:**

1. **Fed leadership transition** — FOMC 8-4 vote (most dissents since 1992). Powell's last meeting. Warsh cleared Senate Banking 13-11. Three hawkish dissenters publicly said next move "could be a cut or a hike." Bond markets are not priced for this.

2. **Earnings blowout** — GOOGL +10% (Cloud +63%), AMZN +5% (AWS +28%), AAPL +3.4% (Services record). Q1 blended EPS growth 27.1% — highest since Q4 2021. 84% beat rate. S&P 500 closed at all-time high 7,230.12; Nasdaq Composite first-ever close above 25,000.

3. **Iran war / Strait of Hormuz** — Still the overriding macro variable. WTI $101.94 close, ~$100.69 Sunday as ceasefire signals emerged. OPEC+ voted 188K b/d increase (Sunday) — first meeting without UAE.

4. **Weekend breaking** — Trump "Project Freedom" announcement for Hormuz ships; Iran diplomatic proposal; Warsh Senate floor vote pending week of May 11 (Powell exits May 15).

**Week ahead:** NFP Friday May 8 is the single most important data point before the June FOMC. No CPI/PCE/GDP/PPI this week — labor data carries unusually high weight. ISM Services + JOLTS Tuesday are the early signals. ALB earnings Wednesday is the lithium thesis check-in.
